   </prolog>
   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>From the left panel under Groups, select <uicontrol>Map Fields</uicontrol>.</p>
            <stepresult> The Map Fields page is displayed.</stepresult>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>From the ribbon at the top of the page, click <uicontrol>New</uicontrol>. </p>
            <stepresult>The New Map Field page is displayed.</stepresult>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Enter "ModifiedOn" in the <uicontrol>Name</uicontrol> field.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Enter "ModifiedOn" in the <uicontrol>Display Name </uicontrol>field.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Enter "DateTime" in the <uicontrol>Type </uicontrol>field.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Enter "modifiedon" in the <uicontrol>Dynamics Field Name </uicontrol>field. </p>
            <p>
               <note type="note">To avoid errors, copy-and-paste the field name from Dynamics 365.</note>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Enter "LastModifiedDate" in the <uicontrol>Power Field Name</uicontrol> field.</p>
            <p>
               <note type="note">To avoid errors, copy-and-paste the field name from Power.</note>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Search and select the <uicontrol>Object Mapping Name</uicontrol>. This is the mapping name of the field's object (for example "Opportunity").</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Save</uicontrol> or <uicontrol>Save &amp; Close</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
